- Maximum 4 tags in frontmatter
- Follow markdown linting rules
- Include proper frontmatter:
  ```yaml
  ---
  layout: post
  title: "Title: Subtitle"
  date: YYYY-MM-DD
  categories: [cat1, cat2]
  tags: [tag1, tag2, tag3, tag4]
  description: "Compelling description"
  ---
  ```

## Writing Style
- Avoid unnecessary adjectives (comprehensive, complete, full, robust)
- Remove filler words (very, really, basically, actually)
- Use active voice
- Get to the point quickly
- Keep code examples focused and well-commented

## Templates
- Standard posts: [_templates/post-template.md](mdc:_templates/post-template.md)
- Tutorials: [_templates/tutorials/step-by-step.md](mdc:_templates/tutorials/step-by-step.md)
- Concept explanations: [_templates/concepts/explanation.md](mdc:_templates/concepts/explanation.md)
- Reviews: [_templates/reviews/review.md](mdc:_templates/reviews/review.md)

## Code Examples
- Always specify language in code blocks
- Include meaningful comments
- Use real-world examples
- Follow language-specific best practices
- Consider accessibility in examples
